gomodel:SYNGO_172  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Ion channel function is shown by expressing channels in CHO cells.\n\nrule: NAS_MFCC-BP\nrationale:\nProtein has voltage-gated ion channel activity and is localized in teh presynaptic membrane (show with high-resolution technique). The inference to term 'voltage-gated ion channel activity involved in regulation of presynaptic membrane potential (GO:0099508)' is trivial and non-controversial.\nPinf_CC:\n[P25122] SyNGO ID 15 (PMID:20857303, EM). Experimental description: Study is done with channels expressed in Chinese hamster ovary (CHO) cells. All antibody studies in this paper are on rat. I assume that they use therefore the rat-gene to express in the CHO's. See MM p.1513: The peptides correspond to a sequence present in the constant region of the rat and mouse Kv3.2 proteins, respectively (residues 171-189 plus an N-terminal cysteine added to facilitate coupling), before the first membrane-spanning domain in an area not conserved among different K\n\n22/2/2017 Pim:\n-The species of the Kcnc1 construct is not stated in the article. I agree with the expert that a **rat** species is assumed safely (other constructs and tissues are rat). This paper is used to annotate rat Kcnc1 by SWIS and RGD GO contricutors. We settle for *rat* species too." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9425-2935" ;
        dc:date           "2018-06-29" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_MF_172" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

